    <note type="biography">
        <p>Writer, jurist, and social reformer. Author of <hi rend="italic">Tom Brown’s school days</hi> (1857), which describes life at Rugby School. Called to the bar, 1848. Liberal MP for Lambeth, 1865; Frome, 1868–74. Appointed Queen’s counsel, 1869. County-court judge, 1882–96. Leading advocate of trade unions. One of the founders of the London Working Men’s College, 1854; principal, 1872–83.</p></note>
